Definition.WordDefinition: Cooky \Cook"y\, n.; pl. {Cookies}. [Cf. D. koek cake, dim. koekje; akin to G. kuchen, E. cake; or cf. OE. coket, prob., a sort of cake, and prob. of French origin.] A small, flat, sweetened cake of various kinds. [1913 Webster]
